{"title":"SBT GRVL On The Road Calabasas with Bahati Foundation 2023","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/03/sbt-grvl-on-the-road-calabasas-with-bahati-foundation-2023/","date":1679679350000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041435-scaled.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"SBT GRVL On The Road Calabasas with Bahati Foundation 2023\" /></figure><figure>When it comes to good times with even better people, <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/?s=sbt%20grvl\" target=\"_blank\">SBT GRVL</a> and the Bahati Foundation know how to host. With bikes, hugs, smiles, and plenty of gravel, it was all fun at Pedalers Fork, even with a bit of light rain. But the real question is, why host such a fun ride? Simple, to get more young athletes to their first gravel race in Steamboat.While Southern California gravel is nothing like the champagne gravel you’ll find while racing SBT GRVL, the two route options meant that there was gravel fun for everyone, and there was no shortage of failure faces there to donate and support. Giant, Liv Cycling, Specialized, Wahoo, Zwift, Ride For Racial Justice, People For Bikes, and many more were all there to support. Better yet, Chamois Butt’r matched all donations, and more than <strong>$5000</strong> was reached this weekend alone.There is still plenty of time to help donate and maybe even make it to one of the <a href=\"https://www.sbtgrvl.com/sbt-grvl-on-the-road\" target=\"_blank\">SBT On The Road events</a>. There might be a ride rolling out of a city near you soon. Make sure you sign up and have as much fun as we did.<br />\nMonterey, CA – Wednesday, April 19th<br />\nBentonville, AR- Saturday/Sunday, April 29-30th<br />\nNew York, NY – Saturday, May 6th<br />\nDenver, CO – Saturday, June 17th<br />\nSan Antonio/Lockhart, TX- Saturday, October 21st</figure>\n<p></p>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6889-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>A few lucky attendees left in style.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6884-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Where do we begin?</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6887-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Ensure you are there early, the raffle goes down before the ride, and the sponsors deliver the goods.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041338-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /><figcaption>Is it really a ride without coffee? Better yet, 10 Speed Coffee.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6888-1340x1787.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1787\" /><figcaption>Even the bottles are fancy.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041346-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6894-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Looks like they saved the best for last.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6896-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Vinh Tran is heading to Steamboat too.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6897-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Local cycling star Phil Gaimon reminded us that even retired, he can eat more cookies than us while he has us on the rivet.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6892-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Someone forgot to check the route, this is a gravel ride, Phil. Gravel pedals should have been the first component swap between the light rain and the mud. These Speedplay pedals have seen countless miles and are still going strong.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6899-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Even these fast dudes debated their bike choice. Bahati rode his Giant trail bike with Fox Live Valve, while Alex Howes was on a road bike and 32mm slicks. I think Bahati made the better choice.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6883-1340x1787.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1787\" /><figcaption>Most everyone else chose a gravel bike, the perfect balance of both for the two route options.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041453-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /><figcaption>Smiles for miles.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041620-1340x2010.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"2010\" /><figcaption>Ride support and this also happened to be the best place to divert around the mud, if only we had known.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041597-1340x2010.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"2010\" /><figcaption>The MTB defiantly had its advantages.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041578-scaled.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1707\" height=\"2560\" /></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6915-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Following Phil Gaimon, Alex Howes, Amy Charity, and Caroline Wreszin is probably a bad idea unless you are super fit, I am not.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6933-1340x1787.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1787\" /><figcaption>So much passion and talent.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041645-1340x2010.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"2010\" /></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6925-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Just a few of us Lauf’n around.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6921-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6922-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6943-1340x1005.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1005\" /><figcaption>Yes, this is LA.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041703-1340x2010.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"2010\" /><figcaption>The final few miles on the road in the rain cleaned most of the mud off, But couldn’t remove the smiles.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041746-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-1041737-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6938-1340x1787.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1787\" /><figcaption>It’s hard to miss this man as he towers over you. Ryan Steers takes credit for many of these photos, and he captured them all while riding the long route too.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/SBT-6890-1340x1787.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1787\" /></figure>","author":"Troy Templin","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"c2133d95327174dfd142e5ac99fea0de51737d45db6a70473dd8fab491b3e807","category":"Cycling"}